messageBody:
I'm writing classes to read Palm PDB files into Java objects. I would like
to have JUnit tests for these classes. The only decent test I can think of
is reading a file into the object model, writing it back to a file, and
doing a file compare.

When doing object models of file formats, have folks come up with other
tests?

thx
a
